capstone.utility

Class LevelBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • capstone.data.Data
      • capstone.utility.LevelBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class LevelBuilder
extends Data
    Takes care of all deserialization and serialization for levels. These methods were previously contained in the Level class. Refactoring is a beautiful thing.
    See Also:

      • _deserializePlayer

        private void _deserializePlayer(java.lang.String key,
                                java.lang.String value,
                                java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Profile> remaining)
        Deserializes a player. The player is added to _players and removed from the remaining map. At the end, there will be only players that haven't been loaded from the session. Some will be put at entrances, the rest will be hidden.
        Parameters:
        key - The key of the property.
        value - The value of the property.
        remaining - The non-mapped set of profiles.

      • _placeAtEntrances

        private void _placeAtEntrances(java.util.Collection<Profile> profiles)
        Takes a collection of profiles and attempts to place them at the entrances of the level. If an entrance is found, a Player is constructed with the point of the entrance and the profile. Profiles that were not matched to entrances are put into the _hidden collection, so that they can be revealed by the Level when the players at the entrances leave their entrance.
        Parameters:
        profiles - The profiles

      • _fetchPage

        private Page _fetchPage()
        Handle fetching the relevant initial page. That page is either the page *one of* (random) the players is on, or else the page at (0, 0) if there are no players.
        Returns:
        The initial Page.

      • _pageSize

        private com.googlecode.lanterna.terminal.TerminalSize _pageSize(int remaining)
        Calculates the TerminalSize that the PageGrid should know of, i.e. the size of one page on the screen. That size is the regular TerminalSize, minus some rows for the level status and status for all the players.
        Parameters:
        remaining - The number of remaining players.
        Returns:
        The proper TerminalSize, with space left for the StatusBar.
